This paper deals with the problem of detecting 419 scams in a cybercriminal community, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR). The paper also involves text processing and machine learning classifiers, which are relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with the issue of bilingualism, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cyberculture (cs.CY).
